http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Seminar-on-careers-in-management-today/article13993053.ece

Secunderabad-based Siva Sivani Institute of Management, Vivekananda Institute of Management, and Gurukul Degree College will host a seminar on ‘Making an international career and changing the job scenario’ here on Monday.The seminar will be useful for management students in their final year, who wish to make international careers in management.Two sessionsThe first session will be held from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. at Gurukul Degree College and the second session will be held at Vivekananda Institute of Management from 3 p.m. to 5 p.m. The entry is free.V.G. Chari, assistant vice-president of Siva Sivani Institute of Management, and P. Ranga Reddy, retired regional general manager of The Hindu, would speak on the subject, a press release said.Secunderabad-based Siva Sivani Institute of Management is organising it